OL,3,CWoman who had three miscarriages calls
OL,4,Cfor baby loss certificates in Wales
OL,6,FThe Welsh Government said it is
OL,7,Fworking with the UK Government to
OL,8,Fextend baby loss certificates to Wales.
OL,10,FEleanor, who now lives in Penarth,
OL,11,Fsaid: "I've got nothing, absolutely
OL,12,Fnothing, there's just an entry
OL,13,Fsomewhere on my medical notes to say I
OL,14,Fwas pregnant and I lost the baby.
OL,16,F"Why should women in Wales not have
OL,17,Fthe same facilities that are now
OL,18,Fthankfully and readily available in
OL,19,Fother parts of the United Kingdom?
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G4/8
